<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:90.74px" class="cls_003"><span class="cls_003">How to Sleep With Headphones</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:117.14px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">A Handbook for Side Sleepers</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:164.78px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Are you a side sleeper? If yes, then we know how difficult it can be to sleep on either side with</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:179.30px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">your headphones. It’s annoying and uncomfortable. While we won’t say that it’s easy to sleep on</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:193.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">either side with earbuds, it is not impossible. However, in the case of over-the-ear or on-the-ear</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:208.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">headphones, you barely have a choice. So, how to sleep with headphones? We know this</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:222.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">question has been on your mind for quite some time now. Don’t worry; we’ve got you covered.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:237.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">In this post, we’ll discuss how to sleep with headphones comfortably. We won’t let your new</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:252.05px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">headphones go waste. Read further to know more.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:284.69px" class="cls_005"><span class="cls_005">Is It Safe to Sleep With Headphones?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:323.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">First things first, it is important to know if sleeping with headphones is the right thing to do.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:337.97px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">According to experts, you can suffer from the Necrosis of the skin inside your ears if you sleep</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:352.49px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">with headphones daily. Necrosis is the death of living cells inside the tissue, due to external</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:367.01px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">factors such as trauma, injury and so on. So, if the earbuds or headphones push too hard</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:381.53px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">against the skin in your ear, too much pressure can lead to Necrosis. Nevertheless, with the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:396.17px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">right headphones, such as the best sleep headphones, such issues are rare.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:425.23px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Therefore, it is safe to sleep with headphones, provided you are using the right headphones and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:439.75px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">wearing them properly. Also, ensure you maintain optimum volume. High volume can damage</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:454.27px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">the eardrum.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:487.03px" class="cls_005"><span class="cls_005">5 Things You Must Do to Sleep With Headphones Comfortably</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:525.67px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Now that you know sleeping with headphones won’t hurt your ears provided you are doing it</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:540.19px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">properly, let’s look at 7 things you should do to ensure you sleep comfortably while wearing your</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:554.71px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">headphones.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:583.90px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  Pick the right headphones</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:598.42px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">First and foremost, make sure you buy the right headphones. You can not buy any headphones</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:612.94px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">if you want to sleep with me. Over-the-ear and on-the-ear headphones are not suitable for</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:627.58px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">sleeping, especially if you are a side sleeper. We recommend you buy in-ear headphones,</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:642.10px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">earphones or earbuds for sleeping. You can also check the best sleep headphones to find the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:656.62px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">right sleep headphones for yourself.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:685.66px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  Ensure the headphones fit accurately</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:802px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Per our suggestion, if you are planning to buy earphones, you must ensure they fit properly</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:85.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">inside your ear, else they’ll keep falling while you are sleeping. Most in-ear headphones and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:100.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">earbuds come with ear tips of different sizes to accommodate your ear size. Also, ensure the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:114.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">earbuds do not exert too much pressure on your ears. If you have tried ear tips of different sizes</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:129.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">and are struggling to find the right fit, you can purchase a set of ear tips separately and see if</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:144.02px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">they fit. Foam tips can be a great alternative to silicone tips that keep slipping from your ear.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:158.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Since they are made of foam, they don’t slip out easily and stay inside your ear when you are</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:173.18px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">changing sides or simply moving in your sleep.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:202.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Read Also: </span><A HREF="https://headphonesproreview.com/do-airpods-fall-out-easily/">Do AirPods Fall Out Easily?</A> </span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:231.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">3.  Try to Sleep on Your Back</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:260.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Sleeping on one side with your earphones or headphones can be a daunting experience.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:274.97px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Therefore, if you want to sleep with your earphones/headphones, it’s best to sleep on your back.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:289.49px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Even though it’s not possible to maintain the same posture throughout while you are sleeping, if</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:304.13px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">you are looking for a comfortable experience, sleeping on the back can be a great idea.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:333.17px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">4.  Be Careful With the Wires</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:362.21px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">If you have wired earphones or headphones, it’s of the utmost importance to ensure the wires</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:376.85px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">don’t get entangled around your neck while you are sleeping. We’ve heard of many accidents</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:391.37px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">where people have died because of the wires getting entangled around their necks while they</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:405.89px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">are fast asleep, choking them. So, be careful with the wires. If possible, we recommend</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:420.43px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">purchasing wireless earbuds and headphones for sleeping.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:449.59px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">5.  Choose the Music Wisely</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:478.63px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">If you want a comfortable experience while sleeping with your headphones, pick the music</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:493.15px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">carefully. You can also try autonomous sensory meridian response (ASMR) to put yourself to</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:507.79px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">sleep. These days, you can easily find the </span><A HREF="https://headphonesproreview.com/best-asmr-headphones/">best ASMR headphones</A> </span><span class="cls_002"> on the market. Avoid</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:522.31px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">listening to loud or high-frequency music as it can hamper your sleep and keep you awake all</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:536.83px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">night. Choose music that is calm and peaceful. You can explore </span><A HREF="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_noise">white noises</A> </span><span class="cls_002"> to get a night of</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:551.35px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">better sleep.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:584.02px" class="cls_005"><span class="cls_005">Type of Sleep Headphones on the Market</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:622.78px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Per our research, these are the two types of earphones/headphones that work wonders for</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:637.30px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">sleeping:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:666.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  Headband Headphones</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:680.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Yes, you read that right. We were also delighted to find the headband headphones. They are</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:695.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">the most comfortable headphones for sleeping. All you need to do is simply wear them around</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:1604px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">your head like a headband and enjoy music without any discomfort. Since the speakers are</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:85.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">inserted in the headband, they won’t fall even if you are moving in your sleep. We tested the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:100.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">headband-type Homder Sleep Headphones and simply loved them. They are comfortable for</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:114.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">sleeping, made of high-quality materials and easily affordable. The sound quality provided by</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:129.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">the tiny, hidden speakers is exceptional.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:158.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  Invisible Earbuds</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:187.70px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Earbuds can be a good choice for sleeping as they are wireless and stay inside your ears</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:202.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">(provided you get the right fitting ear tips). They are known as “invisible earbuds” as they are</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:216.74px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">very tiny and hardly visible when you are sleeping. Out of all the invisible earbuds we tested, we</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:231.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">found the Motorola Verve Buds 300 to be the best. They are comfortable, compact, sleek and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:245.93px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">come with a stylish design. Not only this but the sound quality delivered by the earbuds is also</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:260.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">excellent.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:289.49px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Read Also: </span><A HREF="https://headphonesproreview.com/best-invisible-earbuds/">The 5 Best Invisible Earbuds in 2020</A> </span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:322.25px" class="cls_005"><span class="cls_005">Pros and Cons of Sleeping With Earbuds or Headphones</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:346.37px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">While testing different ASMR and sleep headphones, we got to learn a lot about sleeping with</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:360.89px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">headphones and how it can be good or bad for you. Let’s deep-dive into the advantages and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:375.41px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">disadvantages of sleep headphones.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:406.01px" class="cls_007"><span class="cls_007">Pros</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:439.03px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  Relaxation</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:468.19px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">As already mentioned above, white noises can help a great deal in relaxing your body and mind.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:482.71px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">If you are struggling with a lack of sleep, listening to white noises on your earbuds or</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:497.23px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">headphones can be a great experience. Try it for a couple of weeks and you’ll see how</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:511.75px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">wonderfully white noises work in reducing insomnia and stress. You can also try ASMR. There’s</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:526.39px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">no dearth of ASMR videos on the internet.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:555.43px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  Serotonin Stimulation</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:584.62px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">The chemical “Serotonin” is the magic wand in your brain that stimulates the “good” or “happy”</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:599.14px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">feeling. Listening to music while sleeping is one of the best ways to feel good and wake up</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:613.66px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">happy. A </span><A HREF="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29499311/">study conducted on rats</A> </span><span class="cls_002"> revealed that auditory stimulation by exposure to calming</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:628.18px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">music increases serotonin and dopamine activities in the brain and enhances motor control.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:657.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">3.  Treatment of PTSD</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:671.86px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">A </span><A HREF="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5744879/#:~:text=It%20is%20concluded%20that%20music,rigorous%20empirical%20study%20is%20required.">study conducted by the US National Library of Medicine National Institutes of Health</A> </span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:686.38px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">concluded that music therapy can be useful in reducing symptoms and improving functioning in</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:700.90px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">individuals suffering from Posttraumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD). </span><A HREF="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6299962/">Another study</A> </span><span class="cls_002"> reveals that</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:2406px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">programs with active, music-based instructions can help in reducing depressions in individuals</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:85.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">suffering from PTSD.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:114.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Read Also: </span><A HREF="https://headphonesproreview.com/benefits-of-music-on-learning-and-improving-your-memory/">The Benefits of Music on Learning and Improving Your Memory</A> </span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:145.58px" class="cls_007"><span class="cls_007">Cons</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:178.58px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">When not used correctly, earphones and headphones can lead to issues in your ears (apart</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:193.10px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">from Necrosis, which we’ve already discussed in the first section of the guide), such as:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:222.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  Otitis Externa</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:236.78px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Otitis Externa is the inflammation of the ear canal. In some cases, the skin surrounding the ear</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:251.33px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">canal begins to wear out and fluid gets accumulated in the ear. Most cases of Otitis Externa are</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:265.85px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">related to swimming. Therefore, the condition is also known as “Swimmer's Ear.” Nevertheless,</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:280.49px" class="cls_008"><span class="cls_008"> </span><A HREF="https://www.uofmhealth.org/health-library/swear">prolonged use of headphones</A> <span class="cls_002"> or pressure exerted by the headphones on your ears while you</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:295.01px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">are sleeping can also lead to the inflammation of the ear canal, resulting in Otitis Externa.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:324.05px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  Wax Buildup Inside the Ears</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:338.57px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Earbuds that are inserted deep inside the ears can reduce air circulation in the ear and lead to</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:353.21px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">the accumulation of wax inside the ears. According to an </span><A HREF="https://www.whittierhospital.com/WHMC-Blog/2016/September/Are-Earbuds-Bad-for-My-Ears-.aspx#:~:text=Aside%20from%20carrying%20dirt%20and,Earbuds%20can%20rupture%20your%20eardrums.">article posted by the Whittier Hospital</A> </span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:367.73px" class="cls_008"><span class="cls_008">Medical Center</span><span class="cls_002">, wearing earbuds or headphones can hamper the self-cleaning mechanism of</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:382.25px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">the ears and lead to wax buildup. And, excessive wax accumulation can lead to hearing issues.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:414.91px" class="cls_005"><span class="cls_005">Conclusion</span></div>
